04:42.100 --> 04:48.300
<font color=#38B0DE>Ghost Whisperer
Season 3 Episode 6</font>

04:48.800 --> 04:53.000
I've been looking for occurrences of images
being erased from a photograph.

04:53.100 --> 04:54.100
They're hard to find.

04:54.200 --> 04:56.800
I mean, ghosts popping up, stealing the spotlight?

04:56.900 --> 05:01.700
I mean, they're a dime a dozen.But
somebody actually being knocked from the frame?

05:01.800 --> 05:03.800
That's-- that's unusual.

05:03.900 --> 05:07.100
I'm more interested in the
shape we saw following claudia.

05:07.400 --> 05:09.500
Oh, him. Yeah. Let's call him bob.

05:09.700 --> 05:11.400
Ok. Bob. Why?

05:11.500 --> 05:15.000
'Cause bob riker got my prom date
drunk on peach schnapps.He stole her from me.

05:15.100 --> 05:17.400
Now they're married with 3 kids,
but I don't think they're happy.

05:17.500 --> 05:19.300
Sad. But you've moved on to claudia.

05:19.400 --> 05:20.900
Does she have any idea what happened to her?

05:21.000 --> 05:23.200
Well, she flipped out the second
a camera was pointed at her,

05:23.300 --> 05:26.000
and, well, I'm no expert in composition,

05:26.100 --> 05:29.600
but it sure seems like all the pictures
in her office are kind of lopsided.

05:29.700 --> 05:32.300
- Like she used to be in them?
- More like bob riker took them.

05:32.400 --> 05:33.400
Can a ghost do that?

05:33.500 --> 05:36.500
I mean, transform an existing image or print?

05:36.600 --> 05:40.000
Well, it would help if he had
basic knowledge of photographic principles--

05:40.100 --> 05:43.200
I mean, knowing how light and heat affect pigment.

05:43.300 --> 05:45.600
A photograph is just pixels and colors.

05:45.700 --> 05:48.900
So in theory, he could move them all around
like the piece on an ouija board.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.200
You said he. Is this bob?

05:50.300 --> 05:51.300
No, I'm talking about kevin.

05:51.400 --> 05:54.200
Kevin was one of claudia's graduate students.
He died 2 weeks ago.

05:54.300 --> 05:57.800
And you're just telling me this now?
That is, like, plain withholding.

05:57.900 --> 05:59.600
- What happened to him?
- He died in a car crash.

05:59.700 --> 06:02.600
But I didn't even know until this morning
when I called claudia-- which, by the way,

06:02.700 --> 06:07.000
I was completely breaking my "don't call anyone
for 48 hours after a disastrous date" rule.

06:07.300 --> 06:09.600
I can't imagine how that
came up in a conversation.

06:09.700 --> 06:13.800
Actually, a pretty smooth segue from
"hey, do you know you're invisible?"

06:16.400 --> 06:19.600
That's what makes it a great photograph,
that's the unspoken narrative.

06:19.800 --> 06:21.300
It tells a story.

06:21.600 --> 06:23.900
I will have extended office hours this afternoon,
ok?

06:24.000 --> 06:26.500
But I need to talk to these people.
And joseph, congratulations.

06:26.600 --> 06:28.800
Oh, seriously, professor pollili,
I can't thank you enough.

06:29.000 --> 06:30.300
See you later.

06:30.900 --> 06:33.100
- Hi. I'm claudia.
- Hi. Melinda.

06:33.200 --> 06:34.800
The friend I was telling you about.

06:35.600 --> 06:36.800
What happened to your forehead?

06:36.900 --> 06:39.900
Oh, I was driving home last night
and I clipped a parked car.

06:40.900 --> 06:43.100
- Lucky nobody was hurt.
- Except for you.

06:43.400 --> 06:45.300
Mmm. I don't know where I'm at these days.

06:47.100 --> 06:51.600
All I know is, I came home one day to find
I wasn't in any pictures.

06:51.800 --> 06:53.600
Family, friends, travel--

06:53.700 --> 06:56.800
the photos were still there, but I was gone.

06:57.700 --> 06:59.200
What day was that, exactly?

06:59.300 --> 07:01.700
It was the day after kevin graham died.

07:01.800 --> 07:03.400
Your student.

07:03.500 --> 07:05.900
He died in a car crash.

07:06.000 --> 07:08.400
So talented. Nicest guy.

07:08.500 --> 07:12.600
Last night, did you feel anything strange,
like a presence?

07:12.900 --> 07:14.000
I don't think so.

07:14.100 --> 07:15.800
How well did you know kevin?

07:16.500 --> 07:19.400
Was there any reason for him to be angry with you?

07:20.100 --> 07:23.000
Kevin had the makings of a great photographer.

07:23.100 --> 07:25.300
He had everything that it took...

07:25.800 --> 07:27.900
except for patience.

07:28.000 --> 07:32.300
There was a gallery showing
that he was just desperate to get into.

07:32.800 --> 07:36.200
And he wanted me to make a call on his behalf,
but I told him that he wasn't ready.

07:36.300 --> 07:37.300
Was he upset?

07:37.400 --> 07:40.500
He took it really hard,
like I was telling him he didn't have a future.

07:40.600 --> 07:45.500
But in this business,
you only get one introduction, one shot,

07:45.600 --> 07:47.800
and I didn't want to blow it for him.

07:47.900 --> 07:51.500
I mean, I thought of 100 different ways
that I could have told him, but--

07:51.600 --> 07:55.000
but you thought no matter what the outcome,
it would have always been the same?

07:55.500 --> 07:56.800
I don't know.

07:58.100 --> 08:01.300
I mean, would he have been driving down
a dangerous road at 90 miles an hour

08:01.400 --> 08:03.400
if he thought he had more to live for?

08:03.500 --> 08:04.800
That's every teacher's worst nightmare, you know.

08:04.900 --> 08:07.600
You toss a kid a low grade or a criticism.

08:07.700 --> 08:11.300
Next thing you know, he snaps his cap,
and he wants to off himself or you.

08:11.400 --> 08:12.500
Is that what you're thinking?

08:12.600 --> 08:14.600
Maybe he found a way to do both?

08:14.700 --> 08:16.100
I don't know.

08:16.200 --> 08:18.200
Was this always here?

08:18.300 --> 08:20.700
This translucent shape, do you see it?

08:21.500 --> 08:24.100
- Have you seen it anywhere else?
- Yeah.

08:24.900 --> 08:28.700
Last week, in one of my students' work.
His name's joseph.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.200
Did he know kevin?

08:30.500 --> 08:31.700
Yeah.

08:32.500 --> 08:34.700
Professor pollili knows
everybody in the photo world.

08:34.799 --> 08:36.900
She picks up the phone, and your slides get seen.

08:37.000 --> 08:38.500
So it's that easy?

08:38.700 --> 08:41.400
Well, she has to like your work.

08:41.700 --> 08:44.100
What about kevin?
Did she like his work?

08:44.900 --> 08:46.600
She's tough but fair.

08:46.700 --> 08:51.200
And no disrespect to the dead, because
kevin seemed like a nice guy,a good artist,

08:51.300 --> 08:54.300
but those 2 things, even in combination...

08:54.800 --> 08:56.300
they're not enough. You know what I mean?

08:56.400 --> 08:57.600
I'm not sure I do.

08:58.500 --> 08:59.900
It's so competitive.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.900
It's, like,this tiny market
with too many people to begin with.

09:03.000 --> 09:05.500
And if you don't have what it takes,
what people want...

09:06.400 --> 09:08.200
then you get squeezed out.

09:08.400 --> 09:10.100
And kevin was feeling that squeeze.

09:10.300 --> 09:14.200
Because she made phone calls
on your behalf and not on his?

09:15.200 --> 09:17.200
Yeah. Basically.

09:17.300 --> 09:21.800
She said that you had some photos
with this strange shape in them.

09:21.900 --> 09:23.600
Yeah. Yeah, right. Uh...

09:23.900 --> 09:25.200
that was weird.

09:25.400 --> 09:29.000
I did this ocean series last week-- 
just sand, water...

09:29.100 --> 09:32.300
and this kind of cool translucent thing.

09:32.400 --> 09:34.800
I don't-- I don't know how it happened,
but it looks great.

09:34.900 --> 09:36.400
Can I see them?

09:36.500 --> 09:40.500
- Yeah. Yeah. Um...I could email them to you.
- Thanks.

09:40.600 --> 09:44.100
I promised delia
that I'd check out her inventory spreadsheet.

09:44.200 --> 09:46.800
I also want to download those photos
from that guy joseph.

09:46.900 --> 09:49.300
That's claudia's star pupil, right?
The one your ghost had it out for?

09:49.400 --> 09:51.000
If that's what it's about.

09:51.100 --> 09:53.100
Kevin said his teacher--

09:53.200 --> 09:57.300
I don't know-- helped another grad student
get into more galleries than him.

09:57.500 --> 09:59.600
I don't want to sound harsh,but boo-hoo.

09:59.700 --> 10:00.700
Or boo.

10:00.900 --> 10:02.700
But since when have ghosts become reasonable?

10:02.800 --> 10:04.200
- It just makes me mad.
- What?

10:04.300 --> 10:07.400
That this file's taking so long,
or that he's tormenting his professor?

10:07.500 --> 10:10.900
Oh, because claudia tried to hold him back
until he was ready for the big, bad art world.

10:11.000 --> 10:12.600
I mean, honestly,

10:12.700 --> 10:14.800
that's the worst thing
that's happened to that guy? Seriously?

10:14.900 --> 10:16.900
That's the story he wants told?

10:19.200 --> 10:21.100
Are you seeing this?

10:21.600 --> 10:24.100
I just assumed 
the translucent shape was kevin, but...

10:25.100 --> 10:27.800
well, that doesn't look like any kevin I've met.

10:27.900 --> 10:31.200
Either I have the wrong ghost,
or he's telling a different story.

10:35.700 --> 10:36.700
- Jim saw this?
- Yeah,

10:36.800 --> 10:40.600
and so we clicked back on the same file again,
and then it was just a still photo of the beach.

10:40.700 --> 10:42.400
That's a haunting.
She's made her presence known.

10:42.500 --> 10:44.300
Yeah, but I don't get it.
What does she want us to know?

10:44.400 --> 10:47.700
For starters, she probably wants you to know
you checked the wrong box under "sex of ghost."

10:47.800 --> 10:49.900
Ok, fine, so she's a girl, not a guy.

10:50.000 --> 10:52.900
But this all began with kevin's death,
and I think he's the key.

10:53.200 --> 10:57.100
Maybe claudia knows more than she's saying.

10:57.500 --> 10:59.200
Or even realizes.

11:03.100 --> 11:05.000
Claudia, what happened in here?

11:05.100 --> 11:06.400
She's everywhere.

11:06.500 --> 11:08.500
Here, all my pictures at home.

11:09.100 --> 11:11.700
Joseph came by, and she's in all his pictures, too.

11:11.800 --> 11:14.000
- Who is she?
- I don't know.

11:14.400 --> 11:16.300
Joseph swears he doesn't know, either.

11:17.200 --> 11:19.900
- Why's this happening?
- I don't know.

11:20.000 --> 11:23.000
It's unusual for a ghost to
want to haunt a complete stranger.

11:23.100 --> 11:25.400
Maybe it has something to do with this place.

11:25.500 --> 11:28.000
Well, maybe it's not something you did.

11:28.300 --> 11:29.700
- How well do you know this joseph?
- He's a student.

11:29.800 --> 11:31.300
I'm not involved in his personal life.

11:31.400 --> 11:35.700
Well, did kevin ever talk to you about a girl?
I mean, maybe this joseph's lying.

11:35.800 --> 11:37.600
Maybe it was some kind of romantic triangle--

11:37.700 --> 11:39.700
I told you. I don't know her, ok?

11:39.800 --> 11:42.700
How am I supposed to help you?
I've never seen this girl before in my life.

11:44.500 --> 11:48.300
So this ghost is now showing up
in claudia's pictures and joseph'S.

11:48.400 --> 11:50.500
Claudia seems to be falling apart because of it,

11:50.600 --> 11:53.900
and joseph, as far as I can tell, 
is shrugging it off as weird.

11:54.800 --> 11:56.900
There's still days I wish I was 23

11:57.400 --> 11:59.200
anceconvind d nothing bad
would ever happen to me again.

11:59.300 --> 12:00.600
- You want mustard with this?
- No, thanks.

12:00.700 --> 12:01.700
What's that?

12:01.800 --> 12:04.100
Oh, this, it's just a study guide.

12:04.600 --> 12:08.000
- Isn't it for medical school?
- Well, yeah, technically. Sure.

12:08.500 --> 12:11.000
Ok, so you're gonna go to medical school?
That's great!

12:11.100 --> 12:14.100
Mel, there's a big difference
between going and applying.

12:15.700 --> 12:18.100
The southern michigan catalog,
is that why we got that?

12:18.200 --> 12:19.600
I thought it was just junk mail.

12:19.700 --> 12:21.700
Look, I'm just checking out the possibilities, ok?

12:21.800 --> 12:24.200
Or, in my case, the impossibilities.

12:24.800 --> 12:26.900
Look, the chances of getting in
anywhere are so slim, I thought,

12:27.000 --> 12:30.000
since my dad went there,
 I had an edge being a legacy.

12:30.100 --> 12:33.700
So you're not just gonna change careers,
we might be moving to michigan.

12:33.800 --> 12:35.100
No. I haven't even applied.

12:35.200 --> 12:36.900
What about our life here? And my store.

12:37.000 --> 12:38.900
I mean, were you even going
to talk to me about this?

12:39.000 --> 12:41.000
Of course. I'm just trying to figure it out
by myself at first.

12:41.100 --> 12:45.300
I'm your wife, 
so why aren't you figuring it out with me?

12:46.500 --> 12:48.700
This is a huge conversation, all right?

12:49.100 --> 12:51.800
And it isn't just about your store,
you know that.It's about what you do.

12:51.900 --> 12:54.000
I mean, that's the real discussion, isn't it?

12:54.100 --> 12:56.100
I mean, whether we could ever leave grandview

12:56.200 --> 12:58.900
knowing what we know about this place
and what's underneath it.

12:59.000 --> 13:02.100
That's why I wanted to wait.
Look, I don't even know what I want here.

13:02.200 --> 13:03.800
Or what I even have the right to ask you about.

13:03.900 --> 13:05.300
- Jim...
- let's just talk about it later, all right?

13:05.400 --> 13:08.200
I gotta go to work, 
you gotta cross over a nasty ghost.

13:08.300 --> 13:10.600
Another one, that's what you mean.

13:10.800 --> 13:12.900
No, I didn't mean that. I didn't say that.

13:15.100 --> 13:17.600
Look, I love you, ok? We'll figure this out.

13:22.400 --> 13:24.900
- Is this kevin?
- Yeah.You never met him?

13:25.100 --> 13:28.400
- He was a friend of a friend.
- Well, it's nice of you to help out.

13:29.200 --> 13:31.500
I can't imagine packing up someone's life.

13:31.600 --> 13:34.000
Uh, this girl. Do you know her?

13:34.100 --> 13:35.600
'Cause I'm trying to get in touch with her.

13:35.700 --> 13:38.900
I gave him a lease to sign,
and ran into him getting mail once.

13:39.000 --> 13:40.200
He was always alone.

